# S07-T07: Performance Tests

## Objective
Automated FPS and memory regression checks under load.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `e2e/perf.spec.ts` — runs simulated telemetry burst, asserts ≥30 FPS via `performance.now` deltas.
- Memory snapshot before/after 60s replay run; growth < 10MB.
- Render-budget assertion (rAF interval p95 < 16.7ms).
- Results emitted as Playwright report attachments.

## Steps
1. Build harness that injects synthetic telemetry frames at high rate.
2. Sample frame intervals via `requestAnimationFrame`.
3. Compute p50/p95/p99 + post-run heap diff.
4. Fail test on regression vs. baseline JSON in `e2e/baselines/`.

## Invariants
- 30 FPS minimum (UI_REGULATION & invariants).
- Baselines updated only via explicit PR + reviewer sign-off.
- Tests run on chromium-tablet project (1366×768).
